{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "web:first-corinthians.16",
    "translationId": "web",
    "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
    "chapterNumber": 16,
    "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 16",
    "summary": "Source text for 1 Corinthians 16 in World English Bible."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.16.1",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 16:1",
      "text": "Now concerning the collection for the saints: as I commanded the assemblies of Galatia, you do likewise.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.16.2",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 16:2",
      "text": "On the first day of every week, let each one of you save as he may prosper, that no collections are made when I come.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.16.3",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 16:3",
      "text": "When I arrive, I will send whoever you approve with letters to carry your gracious gift to Jerusalem.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.16.4",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 16:4",
      "text": "If it is appropriate for me to go also, they will go with me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.16.5",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 16:5",
      "text": "I will come to you when I have passed through Macedonia, for I am passing through Macedonia.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.16.6",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 16:6",
      "text": "But with you it may be that I will stay with you, or even winter with you, that you may send me on my journey wherever I go.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.16.7",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 16:7",
      "text": "For I do not wish to see you now in passing, but I hope to stay a while with you, if the Lord permits.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.16.8",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 16:8",
      "text": "But I will stay at Ephesus until Pentecost,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.16.9",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 16:9",
      "text": "for a great and effective door has opened to me, and there are many adversaries.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.16.10",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 16:10",
      "text": "Now if Timothy comes, see that he is with you without fear, for he does the work of the Lord, as I also do.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.16.11",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 16:11",
      "text": "Therefore let no one despise him. But set him forward on his journey in peace, that he may come to me; for I expect him with the brothers.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.16.12",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 16:12",
      "text": "Now concerning Apollos the brother, I strongly urged him to come to you with the brothers, but it was not at all his desire to come now; but he will come when he has an opportunity.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.16.13",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 16:13",
      "text": "Watch! Stand firm in the faith! Be courageous! Be strong!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.16.14",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 16:14",
      "text": "Let all that you do be done in love.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.16.15",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 16:15",
      "text": "Now I beg you, brothers— you know the house of Stephanas, that it is the first fruits of Achaia, and that they have set themselves to serve the saints—",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.16.16",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 16:16",
      "text": "that you also be in subjection to such, and to everyone who helps in the work and labors.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.16.17",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 16:17",
      "text": "I rejoice at the coming of Stephanas, Fortunatus, and Achaicus; for that which was lacking on your part, they supplied.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.16.18",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 16:18",
      "text": "For they refreshed my spirit and yours. Therefore acknowledge those who are like that.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.16.19",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 16:19",
      "text": "The assemblies of Asia greet you. Aquila and Priscilla greet you warmly in the Lord, together with the assembly that is in their house.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.16.20",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 16:20",
      "text": "All the brothers greet you. Greet one another with a holy kiss.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.16.21",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 16:21",
      "text": "This greeting is by me, Paul, with my own hand.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.16.22",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 16:22",
      "text": "If any man doesn’ t love the Lord Jesus Christ, let him be cursed. Come, Lord!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.16.23",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 16:23",
      "text": "The grace of the Lord Jesus Christ be with you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.16.24",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 16:24",
      "text": "My love to all of you in Christ Jesus. Amen.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
